  • Method Details

    • checkSuperClasses

      public MethodFinder.MethodFinderBase checkSuperClasses()
      Used to configure the method finder to include the source class's superclasses when searching for the target method.

      Note that when both checkSuperClasses and checkInterfaces are enabled, the superclasses will take precedence. This means that all super classes (and their interfaces) are evaluated before the interfaces of the source class are evaluated.

      Returns:
      The current method finder instance.

    • ignoreSuperClasses

      public MethodFinder.MethodFinderBase ignoreSuperClasses()
      Used to configure the method finder to ignore the source class's superclasses when searching for the target method. This is the default behavior.
      Returns:
      The current method finder instance.

    • checkInterfaces

      public MethodFinder.MethodFinderBase checkInterfaces()
      Used to configure the method finder to include the source class's interfaces when searching for the target method.

      Note that when both checkSuperClasses and checkInterfaces are enabled, the superclasses will take precedence. This means that all super classes (and their interfaces) are evaluated before the interfaces of the source class are evaluated.

      Returns:
      The current method finder instance.

    • ignoreInterfaces

      public MethodFinder.MethodFinderBase ignoreInterfaces()
      Used to configure the method finder to ignore the source class's interfaces when searching for the target method. This is the default behavior.
      Returns:
      The current method finder instance.
